### 16. 401(k)/403(b)/457(b) accounts not conversion-eligible
**Module:** `models.py` `is_conversion_eligible()`
**Type:** CLARIFICATION_NEEDED

Only IRA-type accounts are eligible. In practice, retirees who have separated from service can roll 401(k) to IRA and then convert. The current model requires users to manually re-type their 401(k) as IRA if they've done a rollover.

**Fix:** Document as known simplification. Optionally, allow employer plan conversions with a note that this assumes rollover has occurred.

**User**. Add this information to ApplicationDetails about conversions.  Conversion to Roth CAN be done for employer plans but requires a conversion to IRA first.  Its just a detail of mechanics.

